# === Apple App Store Connect — NEVER COMMIT (P0 security) ===
# Added 2026-06-07 after auditing committed .p8 keys.
backend/keys/
**/keys/*.p8
*.p8
*.mobileprovision
*.cer
*.p12
*.pem

# EXCEPTION: Apple Root CA G3 is a PUBLIC certificate (downloaded from
# https://www.apple.com/certificateauthority/AppleRootCA-G3.cer) used as
# the trust anchor for StoreKit-2 JWS chain verification on Fly.io. It
# contains NO private material. Without this negation rule the global
# `*.cer` line above silently excludes it from git → it never reaches
# the Fly build context → the Dockerfile's `COPY certs/` lands empty →
# JWS verification crashes with "Apple Root CA certificate not found".
# This is exactly the Build 37 IAP P0 failure mode. Keep this exception.
!backend/certs/AppleRootCA-G3.cer
